"category":"researcher","content":"@shubs and I discovered an instance of Flyte Console on uberinternal.com. After auditing the open source code, we noticed an unauthenticated route for a “CORS proxy”. This was a classic server-side request forgery issue, allowing us to pass an arbitrary request to be performed by the server and read the response. This also allowed reflected cross-site scripting as we could proxy arbitrary HTML documents through it.\n\nWe reported this to both Uber and Flyte, where it was assigned CVE-2022-24856 and quickly resolved.","updated_at":"2022-05-26T22:41:30.055Z","can_view?":true,"can_create?":false,"attachments":[],"user":{"id":566714,"username":"ian","name":"Ian Carroll","bio":"hacking things","cleared":true,"verified":true,"website":"https://ian.sh","location":"Las Vegas, NV","created_at":"2019-04-02T01:44:07.504Z","url":"https://hackerone.com/ian","hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false,"user_type":"hacker","profile_picture_urls":{"small":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/lk26w7vc15x7xwoc7njokw0ks4rn/3cb67cc78dc0cba55b102dd9eca2ee89b206d3e960be830f070583d9070b69ef","medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/lk26w7vc15x7xwoc7njokw0ks4rn/d9695107bfcd68eeb1c9e0912b109cdae9a6c00c0bda6fd4cbd6d9bdb828840a","xtralarge":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/lk26w7vc15x7xwoc7njokw0ks4rn/4ac84fbe897190579a137d0cf55152b233cdd4f9984435bd80ef67e5e51a0586"}}}]}